 ('48', '71', '4', '1', 'en_gb', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Reconfigure.io Brings Cloud-Based Code Deployment to FPGAs\",\"slug\":\"reconfigure-io-brings-cloud-based-code-deployment-to-fpgas\",\"postDate\":1503584996,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"62\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"leadCopy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Manchester, UK, 27th Oct 2016\\u200a\\u2014\\u200aReconfigure.io (http:\\/\\/reconfigure.io), today announced a major leap forward in the FPGA ecosystem with the launch of its platform-as-a-service (PaaS) that enables developers to run code on FPGA\\u2019s as easily as they deploy to servers.\"}}},\"69\":\"\"}}', '2017-08-24 14:29:56', '2017-08-24 14:29:56', 'ee993dd8-63c6-4fa8-b5f7-8ca47ef17e88'),
 ('49', '71', '4', '1', 'en_gb', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Reconfigure.io Brings Cloud-Based Code Deployment to FPGAs\",\"slug\":\"reconfigure-io-brings-cloud-based-code-deployment-to-fpgas\",\"postDate\":1503584940,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"62\":{\"72\":{\"type\":\"leadCopy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Manchester, UK, 27th Oct 2016 &mdash; Reconfigure.io (http:\\/\\/reconfigure.io), today announced a major leap forward in the FPGA ecosystem with the launch of its platform-as-a-service (PaaS) that enables developers to run code on FPGA\\u2019s as easily as they deploy to servers.<\\/p>\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"bodyCopy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Year-over-year improvements in commodity hardware, as described by Moore\\u2019s Law, have dramatically slowed. However, the volume of data and need for performance improvements continue to increase. Experts agree that specialized hardware is the way forward\\u200a&mdash;\\u200adevelopers can leapfrog the limits of commodity hardware with the performance improvements yielded by proper use of FPGA\\u2019s. Reconfigure.io brings the power of FPGA\\u2019s to the modern developer ecosystem.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u201cDevelopers have high expectations in 2016,\\u201d said Reconfigure.io CEO Rob Taylor. \\u201cThe rise of GitHub and Heroku have shown programmers and system administrators that distributing and deploying software can be as easy as a few clicks. Reconfigure.io brings that simplicity to the world of FGPA\\u2019s and thus enables staggering performance improvements.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Programmers using Reconfigure.io write their code in a subset of Google, Inc.\\u2019s Go language and deploy to the Reconfigure.io servers, where a state-of-the-art compiler optimizes and compiles the Go code into an FPGA-compatible form. The Reconfigure.io compiler takes advantage of the Go language\\u2019s built-in support for data parallelism, taking advantage of its language-level semantics to optimize FPGA layout and performance.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Reconfigure.io is in early-stage partnerships with IBM, Xilinx, and Rackspace, three leaders in the cloud and hardware industries. The company is debuting its technology at IBM\\u2019s OpenPOWER Summit Europe in Barcelona, 26th-28th October 2016.<\\/p>\"}}},\"69\":\"\"}}', '2017-08-24 14:30:05', '2017-08-24 14:30:05', 'b4673b3d-9000-453f-8cf6-a56d2db6d420'),
 ('50', '71', '4', '1', 'en_gb', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Reconfigure.io Brings Cloud-Based Code Deployment to FPGAs\",\"slug\":\"reconfigure-io-brings-cloud-based-code-deployment-to-fpgas\",\"postDate\":1503584940,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"62\":{\"72\":{\"type\":\"leadCopy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Manchester, UK, 27th Oct 2016 &mdash; Reconfigure.io (http:\\/\\/reconfigure.io), today announced a major leap forward in the FPGA ecosystem with the launch of its platform-as-a-service (PaaS) that enables developers to run code on FPGA\\u2019s as easily as they deploy to servers.<\\/p>\"}},\"73\":{\"type\":\"bodyCopy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Year-over-year improvements in commodity hardware, as described by Moore\\u2019s Law, have dramatically slowed. However, the volume of data and need for performance improvements continue to increase. Experts agree that specialized hardware is the way forward\\u200a&mdash;\\u200adevelopers can leapfrog the limits of commodity hardware with the performance improvements yielded by proper use of FPGA\\u2019s. Reconfigure.io brings the power of FPGA\\u2019s to the modern developer ecosystem.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u201cDevelopers have high expectations in 2016,\\u201d said Reconfigure.io CEO Rob Taylor. \\u201cThe rise of GitHub and Heroku have shown programmers and system administrators that distributing and deploying software can be as easy as a few clicks. Reconfigure.io brings that simplicity to the world of FGPA\\u2019s and thus enables staggering performance improvements.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Programmers using Reconfigure.io write their code in a subset of Google, Inc.\\u2019s Go language and deploy to the Reconfigure.io servers, where a state-of-the-art compiler optimizes and compiles the Go code into an FPGA-compatible form. The Reconfigure.io compiler takes advantage of the Go language\\u2019s built-in support for data parallelism, taking advantage of its language-level semantics to optimize FPGA layout and performance.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Reconfigure.io is in early-stage partnerships with IBM, Xilinx, and Rackspace, three leaders in the cloud and hardware industries. The company is debuting its technology at IBM\\u2019s OpenPOWER Summit Europe in Barcelona, 26th-28th October 2016.<\\/p>\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"imageFile\":[\"61\"]}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=CfmlsDW3Z4c\"}}},\"69\":\"\"}}', '2017-08-25 13:01:19', '2017-08-25 13:01:19', 'e85773bb-b1fc-447f-b370-55479d020e4b'),
